organization: Oxford Spring School in Advanced Research Methods organization_url: â€˜https://www.politics.ox.ac.uk/spring-school/oxford-spring-school-in-advanced-research-methods.htmlâ€™ title: Machine Learning url: â€˜https://www.politics.ox.ac.uk/spring-school/course-outline.html?schoolid=517â€™ certificate_url: â€™â€™ date_start: â€˜2021-04-19â€™ date_end: â€˜2021-04-23â€™ description: â€˜Computational techniques broadly referred to as â€œmachine learningâ€ (ML) are attracting increasing attention in the social sciences. This course will introduce students to the fundamental theories and concepts used across ML techniques (e.g maximum likelihood estimation, classification, overfitting, and cross-validation), and how to apply various popular ML techniques (e.g.Â LASSO, random forests, bayesian additive regression trees, and neural networks). This course will also pay particular attention to inferential problems regarding how best to use ML methods in social science contexts and discuss practical issues (e.g.Â computational power and parallelisation). Students on this course are required to be familiar with probability and statistics (OLS, hypothesis testing, logistic regression) and to have basic knowledge of the R programming language.â€™
organization: Inter-university Consortium for Political and Social Research (ICPSR) organization_url: â€˜https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/web/pages/sumprog/scholarships/winners-2020.htmlâ€™ title: Advanced Network Analysis, and Data Science and Text Analysis url: â€˜https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/web/pages/sumprog/biblio/2020/â€™ certificate_url: â€˜https://www.coursera.orgâ€™ date_start: â€˜2020-07-14â€™ date_end: â€˜2020-08-20â€™ description: â€˜The ICPSR Summer Program provides rigorous, hands-on training in statistical techniques, research methodologies, and data analysis.â€™
organization: Summer Institute in Computational Social Science (SICSS-Helsinki) organization_url: â€˜https://sicss.io/2018/helsinki/â€™ title: Computational Social Science url: â€™â€™ certificate_url: â€˜https://sicss.io/2018/helsinki/peopleâ€™ date_start: â€˜2018-06-17â€™ date_end: â€˜2018-06-30â€™ description: â€˜The purpose of the Summer Institute is to bring together graduate students, postdoctoral researchers, and beginning faculty interested in computational social science. The Summer Institute is for both social scientists (broadly conceived) and data scientists (broadly conceived). Topics covered include text as data, website scraping, digital field experiments, non-probability sampling, mass collaboration, and ethics.â€™













